  "response": "Here's an insider perspective on working as a consultant at Capgemini India for an IIT/IIM graduate:\n\nTypical Work Experience:\n- Entry-level consulting/technology roles\n- Initial salary ranges from \u20b96-12 lakhs per annum\n- Technology/business process consulting projects\n- Work involves client interactions, solution design, implementation\n\nPositives:\n- Reputed multinational company\n- Good learning opportunities\n- Exposure to diverse industries\n- Global work environment\n- Reasonable work-life balance\n- Structured training programs\n- International project possibilities\n\nChallenges:\n- Initial work might feel less challenging compared to academic rigor\n- Repetitive project assignments\n- Some bureaucratic processes\n- Travel requirements\n- Performance pressure\n- Not always cutting-edge technological work\n\nSkill Development:\n- Project management\n- Client communication\n- Technical problem-solving\n- Domain knowledge\n- Soft skills enhancement\n\nCareer Progression:\n- Potential for internal growth\n- Opportunities for specialization\n- Possibility of moving to different practice areas\n- Can serve as stepping stone for future opportunities\n\nImportant Note: Individual experiences can vary significantly based on specific role, project, team, and personal performance.",
